      "writtenOn": "2026-07-15T07:32:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If the test fails before Create Directory ${fw_verify_dir} (e.g. OperatingSystem.File Should Exist raises an error on line 284), the teardown will attempt to remove a directory that does not exist. Robot Framework\u0027s Remove Directory raises Directory \u0027${FW_VERIFY_DIR}\u0027 does not exist in that case, causing a secondary teardown failure.\n\n\nUse a conditional remove:\n```\n[Teardown]  Run Keyword And Ignore Error  Remove Directory  ${FW_VERIFY_DIR}  recursive\u003dTrue\n```\nOr use OperatingSystem.Directory Should Not Exist guard before Remove, or add ignore_if_missing\u003dTrue when RF supports it.\n\nTeardown failures obscure the real failure reason and make test result analysis harder.",
      "revId": "3f558796fd6509611dee06d4bdcab0d121b5e4a6",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
