      "writtenOn": "2026-07-15T07:32:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Verify BMC Backup Firmware Version calls Get BMC Firmware Version backup and immediately passes the result to Verify Version On GUI ${backup_version}. If the FirmwareInventory contains no backup BMC entry, ${backup_version} will be ${EMPTY}. Wait Until Keyword Succeeds 1 min 5 sec Page Should Contain ${EMPTY} will likely pass vacuously (empty string is always \"contained\") or produce a misleading pass. The test would report success even when the backup version is genuinely absent.\n\nAdd a guard in Get BMC Firmware Version or in the calling test:\n\n```\n# In Get BMC Firmware Version, replace the final RETURN with:\nFail  msg\u003dNo backup BMC firmware version found in FirmwareInventory\n\n# OR in Verify BMC Backup Firmware Version, add after Get BMC Firmware Version:\nShould Not Be Empty  ${backup_version}\n...  msg\u003dNo backup BMC firmware version found — cannot verify GUI display\n```\n\nA test that passes when the feature under test is absent provides false confidence. The backup version verification test must fail loudly when no backup entry exists.",
      "revId": "3f558796fd6509611dee06d4bdcab0d121b5e4a6",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
