      "writtenOn": "2026-07-15T07:32:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If the \"Update started\" toast auto-dismisses within the 10-second close window, Wait Until Element Is Visible ${xpath_update_started_toast_close} will time out and the keyword will fail spuriously. The same pattern applies to the \"Verify update\" toast close sequence (line 566).\n\nI would recommend to use Run Keyword And Ignore Error or a conditional close for the toast close step, or verify the toast auto-dismiss timeout is longer than 10 seconds in the target WebUI:\n\n```\n# Close only if still visible (guard against auto-dismiss)\n${toast_visible}\u003d  Run Keyword And Return Status\n...  Element Should Be Visible  ${xpath_update_started_toast_close}\nIF  ${toast_visible}\n    Click Element  ${xpath_update_started_toast_close}\n    Wait Until Element Is Not Visible  ${xpath_update_started_toast}  timeout\u003d10s\nEND\n```\n\nHard-coding a 10-second visibility wait for a close button that may have auto-dismissed causes spurious test failures unrelated to the firmware update itself. This is a flakiness source.",
      "revId": "3f558796fd6509611dee06d4bdcab0d121b5e4a6",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
